					<head>Genesis</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420" rend="visible">
						<summary>Genesis with Targum Onḳelos and Sa'adia Gaon's Arabic translation in Hebrew characters, with superlinear punctuation.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr jrb">Hebrew, Aramaic, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420">
							<locus from="1r" to="73v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he">בראשית </title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Bereshit</title>
							<title xml:lang="en">Genesis</title>
							<note>
								<p>Fragments of Genesis, chapters: 2:24-5:14; 6:18-8:5; 9:16-10:32; 11:19-27:34; 28:3-32:11; 32:14-37:3; 37:8-37:14; 38:29-42:19; 46:5-47:7; 48:18-49:26.</p>
								<p>Folios 72r-73v contain chapter 31:40-53 and chapter 9:25-10:15; the former is stylistically related to the rest of the manuscript, the latter has a style of its own; both these leaves have the targum and Arabic translation after each verse like the rest of the manuscript, but the contents are duplicates of parts contained in folios 1r-71v.</p>
								<p>Fragments of Genesis, each verse being followed by the Targum of Onḳelos and Sa'adia's Arabic translation in the Hebrew characters.</p>
								<p>Text and Targum have the simple superlinear punctuation.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex, text written in square Yemenite script of about 14th or 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>73 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>310</height>
										<width>230</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>240</height>
										<width>200</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>73 (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end)</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Hard to establish since many folios/quires are missing. Extant quires are mostly of 6 leaves.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Many pages mutilated, especially folios 1-11.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2 " ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25">
									<p>Visible pricking and ruling with hard-point.</p>
									<p>Writing in two columns, with superlinear masoretic punctuation.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc>
							<summary>Square Yemenite handwriting; folio 73r-73v is probably later than than the whole manuscript.</summary>
